WEBVTT

00:03.537 --> 00:06.540
You got a baby coming.
A car seat just won't fit.

00:06.574 --> 00:08.576
We tried it on the turnpike
with a watermelon.

00:08.609 --> 00:12.180
If it's okay, Lou, I'd like
a few moments alone with her.

00:12.213 --> 00:16.884
**

00:16.917 --> 00:18.719
[ Whistles ]

00:18.752 --> 00:20.588
That's a 30-footer.

00:20.621 --> 00:22.490
35.

00:22.523 --> 00:25.393
Calvin, General Manager
of Kareem Abdul-Jabbar Motors.

00:25.426 --> 00:28.762
Oh, I get it. [ Chuckles ]
Like the NBA legend.

00:28.796 --> 00:31.199
You guys are just copying
Shaq Motors across town.

00:31.232 --> 00:33.434
No, no.
He's copying me.

00:33.467 --> 00:34.735
[ Gasps ]

00:34.768 --> 00:37.338
Always has.

00:37.371 --> 00:40.007
I'm a Laker center.
He's a Laker center.

00:40.040 --> 00:43.611
I buy a car lot.
He buys a car lot.

00:43.644 --> 00:45.613
I star in a movie.

00:45.646 --> 00:48.716
He stars in..."Shazam."

00:48.749 --> 00:50.251
It was "Kazaam."

00:50.284 --> 00:52.052
I got this, Melvin.

00:52.086 --> 00:53.254
[ Whispering ]
It's Calvin.

00:53.287 --> 00:54.588
Kareem, I didn't know
you owned a car lot.

00:54.622 --> 00:56.357
I come down here
every so often

00:56.390 --> 00:57.791
to make sure things
are going right.

00:57.825 --> 00:59.427
Oh, yeah.
It's a real morale boost

00:59.460 --> 01:02.363
for those that work here
the other 360 days a year.

01:02.396 --> 01:05.433
Morale was boosted pretty high
when I dropped those 50 skyhooks

01:05.466 --> 01:07.801
on your co-ed
recreation-league game.

01:07.835 --> 01:10.070
Still didn't
play no defense.

01:10.104 --> 01:11.905
So, you interested
in this RV?

01:11.939 --> 01:13.741
Oh. Oh, no.
I'm just, uh,

01:13.774 --> 01:15.075
helping my friend
trade in his car.

01:16.076 --> 01:19.413
Long may you run, Cherry.

01:19.447 --> 01:21.715
Long may you run.

01:21.749 --> 01:22.583
[ Smooches ]

01:24.618 --> 01:26.954
Well, look, why don't we
just go for a test drive?

01:26.987 --> 01:30.090
[ Sighs ] I don't know.

01:33.161 --> 01:34.795
Kareem:
All the comforts of home,

01:34.828 --> 01:37.498
except your address
is Adventure, USA.

01:37.531 --> 01:40.434
I have always wanted to take
the family out on the pavement,

01:40.468 --> 01:42.903
road-trip it like
one of those families on TV.

01:42.936 --> 01:44.505
Close your eyes, Louis.

01:44.538 --> 01:48.242
Turn the keys. Embark.

01:48.276 --> 01:51.111
[ "Full House"
theme song plays ]

01:51.145 --> 01:52.413
* Everywhere you look

01:52.446 --> 01:53.781
* Everywhere you go

01:53.814 --> 01:54.948
* There's a heart

01:54.982 --> 01:56.116
* There's a heart

01:56.150 --> 01:58.586
* A hand to hold onto

01:58.619 --> 02:00.087
* Everywhere you look

02:00.120 --> 02:01.455
* Everywhere you go

02:01.489 --> 02:06.126
* There's a face
of somebody who needs you *

02:06.160 --> 02:09.096
* Everywhere you look

02:09.129 --> 02:10.864
* When you're lost out there

02:10.898 --> 02:13.201
* And you're all alone

02:13.234 --> 02:17.971
* A light is waiting
to carry you home *

02:18.005 --> 02:20.140
* Everywhere you look

02:22.176 --> 02:25.012
* Everywhere you look

02:25.045 --> 02:27.181
* Shoo-ba-doo-ba-baba-dow

02:28.382 --> 02:30.351
The Huangs
across America.

02:31.919 --> 02:33.954
So, cash?
Or how does this work?

02:33.987 --> 02:35.856
Louis!

02:35.889 --> 02:38.058
Honey's in labor!
Sh-- Hey.

02:38.091 --> 02:40.060
The co-pilot
from "Airplane."

02:40.093 --> 02:41.695
C-Come on!
We gotta go!

02:43.731 --> 02:45.899
This close to a sale.

02:45.933 --> 02:48.369
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:48.402 --> 02:49.570
* Fresh off the boat

02:49.603 --> 02:51.472
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

02:51.505 --> 02:53.574
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

02:53.607 --> 02:54.908
* Fresh off the boat

02:54.942 --> 02:57.077
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

02:57.110 --> 02:58.679
* But I know where I'm goin'

02:58.712 --> 03:01.315
* I'm fresh off the boat

03:01.349 --> 03:04.985
**

03:05.018 --> 03:07.921
Can you believe it?
Our baby boy came out a girl.

03:07.955 --> 03:09.857
[ Chuckles ] What a show.

03:09.890 --> 03:11.024
It doesn't happen much,

03:11.058 --> 03:13.261
but the technician
misread the sonogram.

03:13.294 --> 03:14.328
And what we thought was
his deedle-doo

03:14.362 --> 03:16.196
was actually a thing-a-ma-which.
[ Chuckles ]

03:16.230 --> 03:17.598
Umbilical cord.
Yeah.

03:17.631 --> 03:19.833
So, now we need
a girl's name.

03:19.867 --> 03:21.835
Did you already have
a boy name picked out?

03:21.869 --> 03:24.238
Well, Marvin insisted
on a nautical theme,

03:24.272 --> 03:26.940
so we were down to two --
Jonah and...

03:26.974 --> 03:28.041
Ishmael.

03:28.075 --> 03:29.777
So a happy miracle, indeed.

03:29.810 --> 03:32.380
[ Chuckles ] And just think,
your baby's due tomorrow.

03:33.581 --> 03:35.449
Your book -- "A Case
of a Knife to the Brain."

03:35.483 --> 03:39.253
Oh, gosh. [ Sighs ]
Already? I almost forgot.

03:39.287 --> 03:42.055
You did send birth announcements
to the entire HOA.

03:42.089 --> 03:44.292
Oh, that was a joke.
[ Chuckles ]

03:44.325 --> 03:47.628
Of course I don't think
my book is an actual baby...

03:47.661 --> 03:49.597
though I did spend
more than nine months on it.

03:49.630 --> 03:51.231
What did you mean by
"deedle-doo"?

03:54.134 --> 03:54.868
[ Emergency brake engages ]

03:54.902 --> 03:56.470
So, about your baby sister --

03:56.504 --> 03:59.239
No, we're not naming her
"Jamiroquai."

03:59.273 --> 04:01.074
Alright. We'll circle back
to this in a week

04:01.108 --> 04:02.310
when you're
not so close to it.

04:02.343 --> 04:04.945
Yeah, about that.

04:04.978 --> 04:06.747
We need to have a talk.

04:06.780 --> 04:07.915
A Saturn talk.

04:07.948 --> 04:09.617
Whoa.

04:09.650 --> 04:10.984
[ Sunroof closes ]

04:11.018 --> 04:12.653
Saturn secure.

04:12.686 --> 04:14.488
What happens in here
stays in here.

04:14.522 --> 04:15.523
Shoot.

04:17.691 --> 04:20.328
I'm moving to New York with
my mom, and I got into this
school that teaches fashion,

04:20.361 --> 04:21.762
and I don't think
I can pass it up.

04:23.431 --> 04:26.767
[ Sighs ] Sorry.
I know this sucks.

04:26.800 --> 04:28.602
That's...

04:28.636 --> 04:29.603
awesome!

04:29.637 --> 04:30.838
It is?

04:30.871 --> 04:32.473
Totally! New York City?

04:32.506 --> 04:35.609
You can chill out in the park,
order pizzas at 3:00 a.m.,

04:35.643 --> 04:38.011
and Beastie Boys songs
will make a lot more sense now.

04:38.045 --> 04:39.580
Why is there no sleep
till Brooklyn?

04:39.613 --> 04:41.181
Well, you're
about to find out.

04:41.214 --> 04:42.950
Wow. I thought this talk

04:42.983 --> 04:44.485
was gonna be
a whole lot tougher.

04:44.518 --> 04:46.654
Please. You know me
better than that.

04:46.687 --> 04:49.323
What? Did you think I was gonna
start crying or something?

04:49.357 --> 04:51.191
[ Fakes crying, laughs ]

04:54.995 --> 04:57.030
* Happy Book Day to you

04:57.064 --> 04:58.832
* Happy Book Day to you

04:58.866 --> 05:00.167
* Happy --

05:00.200 --> 05:01.769
I have a reading
for my novel today,

05:01.802 --> 05:03.236
and I need to decide
on a passage.

05:05.305 --> 05:08.609
"Snap! And suddenly
the only sound was the rope,

05:08.642 --> 05:12.279
creaking under his weight
and the fading pendulum scrape

05:12.312 --> 05:15.649
of his steel-toe boots
against the hickory planks."

05:15.683 --> 05:17.050
Powerful.

05:17.084 --> 05:18.619
Do you like that passage

05:18.652 --> 05:21.321
or the one where they find
the paperboy's bloody bike?

05:21.355 --> 05:23.491
Hmm, tough call.
They're both great. [ Chuckles ]

05:23.524 --> 05:24.558
Uh, where is this reading?

05:24.592 --> 05:26.026
The bookstore.

05:26.059 --> 05:28.328
My publisher thinks
it might help boost sales,

05:28.362 --> 05:31.899
which could lead to TV spots,
a book tour...maybe even Oprah.

05:31.932 --> 05:34.134
[ Gasps ] The Big "O."

05:34.167 --> 05:36.136
[ Chuckles ]
I-I mean, "big" like a star.

05:36.169 --> 05:37.638
She actually looks
great now.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.707
And she did before, too.

05:39.740 --> 05:41.642
[ Clears throat ]
Um, this is great.

05:41.675 --> 05:43.644
Uh, I'll get the boys,
and we'll all go to the reading.

05:43.677 --> 05:45.513
But it's my job.

05:45.546 --> 05:47.080
I don't go to the restaurant
and stare at you.

05:47.114 --> 05:48.549
Remember?

05:48.582 --> 05:50.418
We found that it didn't
improve your productivity.

05:50.451 --> 05:52.920
But this is your big day,
and it'll be good for the boys.

05:52.953 --> 05:55.923
They learn by watching us,
and they should see how
your hard work pays off.

05:55.956 --> 05:59.092
You would just be taking up
space from actual book-buyers.

05:59.126 --> 06:01.228
Plus, if I want to read
the graphic sex scenes,

06:01.261 --> 06:03.664
I need to feel comfortable
doing all the sound effects.

06:03.697 --> 06:07.200
**

06:09.302 --> 06:11.271
"So You Wanna Be
a Psychiatrist"?

06:11.304 --> 06:13.441
You know how I plan
to become Doctor President.

06:13.474 --> 06:15.042
Well, I always assumed
I'd be a surgeon.

06:15.075 --> 06:16.243
The respect...

06:16.276 --> 06:17.845
The mastery
of fine motor skills...

06:17.878 --> 06:19.413
The ladies.

06:19.447 --> 06:21.849
But after spending three hours
in the hospital

06:21.882 --> 06:23.083
visiting Honey's baby,

06:23.116 --> 06:24.418
I don't think
I can stand the smell.

06:24.452 --> 06:25.986
Can you mail a hot dog?

06:27.320 --> 06:29.723
I'm making a list of
stuff I want Nicole to
send me from New York --

06:29.757 --> 06:31.258
a Statue of Liberty
lighter,

06:31.291 --> 06:33.594
whatever a knish is,
a bullet.

06:33.627 --> 06:35.863
Any ideas for her
going-away gift?

06:35.896 --> 06:38.231
I'm always game to power-browse
Things Remembered at the mall.

06:38.265 --> 06:39.933
Why would I get her
a gift?

06:39.967 --> 06:41.702
Because she's your friend.

06:41.735 --> 06:43.303
I have tons of friends.

06:43.336 --> 06:44.472
I'm not trying
to dole out prizes

06:44.505 --> 06:45.706
every time one of them
skips town.

06:45.739 --> 06:47.207
But Nicole is different.

06:47.240 --> 06:49.042
Oh, because she's a chick?

06:49.076 --> 06:50.277
That's sexist, homey.

06:50.310 --> 06:53.046
No, I mean,
you two are so close.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.582
Aren't you sad
she's moving?

06:54.615 --> 06:55.883
Sad? Pfft.

06:55.916 --> 06:57.384
She's only leaving
for school,

06:57.417 --> 06:59.820
and she'll be back
on the holidays and stuff.

06:59.853 --> 07:01.589
Guys,
it's not a big deal.

07:01.622 --> 07:03.423
**

07:03.457 --> 07:05.325
"The lady doth protest
too much, methinks."

07:05.358 --> 07:08.729
Uh, can we stay on Eddie
for a second?

07:08.762 --> 07:10.964
I think he's pretending he
doesn't care Nicole is leaving.

07:10.998 --> 07:12.432
Yeah, that's what I --

07:12.466 --> 07:15.168
He's in denial.
I read about this in my book.

07:15.202 --> 07:17.471
He needs to admit he's sad
and talk about his feelings.

07:17.505 --> 07:19.306
Or he might dissociate
completely

07:19.339 --> 07:21.408
and chop us all up
in our sleep.

07:21.441 --> 07:24.311
That's an extreme example
in here, but it does happen.

07:24.344 --> 07:27.114
Boys, get ready. We're gonna
surprise Mom at her reading.

07:28.482 --> 07:29.750
We're going
to the bookstore.

07:29.783 --> 07:30.751
Hallelujah!

07:30.784 --> 07:32.953
Get ready to feast,
brain!

07:32.986 --> 07:35.155
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:35.188 --> 07:36.323
Wow, look at this line.

07:36.356 --> 07:38.458
It's like Mommy
is Space Mountain.

07:38.492 --> 07:41.261
Sorry. We're not letting
anyone else in today.

07:41.294 --> 07:43.030
Fire code.

07:43.063 --> 07:44.632
We'll have plenty
of books tomorrow.

07:44.665 --> 07:45.933
[ Crowd groans ]

07:45.966 --> 07:47.367
You know what? That's fine.

07:47.400 --> 07:48.769
She's doing it, boys.

07:48.802 --> 07:50.070
We'll just surprise her
back home.

07:51.371 --> 07:52.806
You made me put on
my dress shorts.

07:54.374 --> 07:56.577
[ Excited, indistinct chatter ]

08:02.683 --> 08:07.655
**

08:07.688 --> 08:10.190
I'm a failure.

08:15.362 --> 08:19.700
**

08:19.733 --> 08:21.635
Hey, Jessica.

08:21.669 --> 08:23.136
We know what happened
at the reading.

08:23.170 --> 08:24.404
You do?

08:24.437 --> 08:26.506
We went there
to surprise you.

08:26.540 --> 08:29.209
Look, it isn't easy
to say, but I --

08:29.242 --> 08:31.912
Absolutely killed it!
[ Chuckles ]

08:31.945 --> 08:33.647
It was so crowded
we couldn't even get in.

08:33.681 --> 08:36.550
We were so excited,
we made you...

08:36.584 --> 08:39.419
A case of a knife
to the brain.

08:39.452 --> 08:40.888
Cake!

08:40.921 --> 08:42.522
A cake of a knife
to the brain!

08:42.556 --> 08:44.024
One line, Ma.

08:45.759 --> 08:47.260
[ Chuckles ]

08:47.294 --> 08:48.862
Well,
tell us all about it.

08:48.896 --> 08:53.366
**

08:53.400 --> 08:55.168
What can I say?
The book is a hit.

08:55.202 --> 08:57.070
-Alright!
-Yes, Mom!

08:57.104 --> 08:58.538
But it's not a big deal.

08:58.572 --> 09:00.708
You're right.
It is a very big deal.

09:00.741 --> 09:03.343
Boys, your mother's hard work
has led to this great success.

09:03.376 --> 09:06.379
How big a hit are we talking?
Are we rich?

09:06.413 --> 09:07.514
Can we get a pet puma?!

09:07.547 --> 09:09.049
Let's just say the store

09:09.082 --> 09:11.551
has never sold as many copies
on a first day.

09:11.585 --> 09:14.554
[ Chuckles ] So, a-a book tour?
TV interviews?

09:14.588 --> 09:16.924
[ Gasps ] Oh, my God.
Is Regis on the table?

09:16.957 --> 09:18.358
I don't want to jinx it,

09:18.391 --> 09:20.728
so just don't go crazy
spending money.

09:20.761 --> 09:23.463
Yeah, nobody "MC Hammer"
this thing.

09:23.496 --> 09:26.099
**

09:26.133 --> 09:28.702
The river on the east side
is the East River,

09:28.736 --> 09:31.238
but the river on the west
is the Hudson?

09:31.271 --> 09:32.873
Good luck, Nicole.

09:32.906 --> 09:34.407
At least he's thinking
about her.

09:34.441 --> 09:35.609
That's good, right?

09:35.643 --> 09:38.278
I'm afraid not.
It's classic sublimation.

09:38.311 --> 09:40.748
His denial has turned
into productivity.

09:40.781 --> 09:42.482
He's losing
his sense of self.

09:42.515 --> 09:44.317
When has Eddie ever researched
for pleasure?

09:44.351 --> 09:45.786
My God.

09:45.819 --> 09:47.587
He needs to face
his feelings soon,

09:47.621 --> 09:50.457
or when it finally hits him,
he'll lash out at someone.

09:50.490 --> 09:52.059
Chop. Chop.

09:52.092 --> 09:53.627
[ Breathes deeply ]

09:53.661 --> 09:55.528
Hey, dawg.

09:56.864 --> 09:59.099
Evan and I were just
talking about Nicole.

09:59.132 --> 10:01.134
Your best friend
who's moving away.

10:01.168 --> 10:03.136
You two sure have had
some great times together.

10:03.170 --> 10:04.905
Mm.

10:04.938 --> 10:08.108
* Back in the days when I was
young, I'm not a kid anymore *

10:08.141 --> 10:10.978
* But some days I sit
and wish I was a kid again *

10:11.011 --> 10:14.414
* Back in the days when I was
young, I'm not a kid anymore *

10:14.447 --> 10:16.283
* But some days I sit
and wish I was a kid again *
[ Eddie screams ]

10:16.316 --> 10:19.119
* And everybody say
* I remember way back when

10:19.152 --> 10:22.155
* And everybody say
* I remember way back when

10:22.189 --> 10:25.458
* And everybody say
* I remember way back when

10:25.492 --> 10:26.593
* What?
* Back in the day

10:26.626 --> 10:28.962
* When?
* Back in the day

10:28.996 --> 10:32.132
Yeah, we have had
some great times.

10:32.165 --> 10:34.467
Thanks for reminding me,
guys.

10:34.501 --> 10:36.636
There's so much stuff I
have to get out of her
car before she goes --

10:36.670 --> 10:39.206
my CD Player, Bootyman hat,

10:39.239 --> 10:41.308
drive-thru window
gorilla mask.

10:41.341 --> 10:43.844
For our door --
padlock or dead bolt?

10:43.877 --> 10:44.878
[ Sighs ]

10:44.912 --> 10:46.513
[ Birds chirping ]

10:48.081 --> 10:50.650
Louis! What did I tell you
about spending money?

10:50.684 --> 10:53.687
There isn't even enough room
in the pantry for all of this.

10:53.721 --> 10:56.523
True.
But there is room...

10:56.556 --> 10:58.225
in here.

10:58.258 --> 11:00.728
[ Horn honks
"Full House" theme ]

11:00.761 --> 11:04.131
What...is...this?

11:04.164 --> 11:07.134
It's a 1998 NationWheeler
with all the bells and whistles.

11:07.167 --> 11:08.368
Why is this?

11:08.401 --> 11:10.971
Now we can all go
on your book tour as a family.

11:11.004 --> 11:12.873
Finally take that
road trip across America

11:12.906 --> 11:14.007
we've always talked about.

11:14.041 --> 11:15.375
We can see
the Heartland.

11:15.408 --> 11:16.476
And the regions
of the South

11:16.509 --> 11:18.345
once decimated
by the boll weevil.

11:18.378 --> 11:20.347
How much did this
house-truck cost?

11:20.380 --> 11:22.015
I knew that would come up,
but don't worry.

11:22.049 --> 11:22.916
It's a business write-off.

11:22.950 --> 11:27.587
**

11:27.620 --> 11:29.356
Now as we drive
across the land,

11:29.389 --> 11:32.325
everyone will know best-selling
author Jessica Huang is aboard.

11:32.359 --> 11:34.527
Is that my
driver's license photo?

11:35.796 --> 11:38.832
Um, so, what do you say?
Huangs across America?

11:38.866 --> 11:44.504
**

11:44.537 --> 11:45.505
Sure.

11:45.538 --> 11:46.606
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

11:47.941 --> 11:49.442
I live here now.

11:49.476 --> 11:53.346
**

11:53.380 --> 11:55.582
I remember packing for
the big city around your age.

11:55.615 --> 11:56.683
Of course, back then
all you needed

11:56.716 --> 11:59.419
was a bar of soap
and your wits.

11:59.452 --> 12:01.454
We're gonna miss you,
Nicole.

12:01.488 --> 12:02.956
And so will
little Maria.

12:02.990 --> 12:04.958
[ Baby crying in distance ]

12:04.992 --> 12:07.560
Ah, sounds like
Coral's stirring.

12:07.594 --> 12:08.962
I'll go get Coral.

12:08.996 --> 12:11.264
No, no. Stay.
I'll get Maria.

12:11.298 --> 12:13.366
[ Crying continues ]

12:13.400 --> 12:14.167
Mm!

12:15.402 --> 12:18.271
[ Door opens, closes ]

12:18.305 --> 12:21.041
Hey. Still going
to New York, huh?

12:21.074 --> 12:23.043
Yeah. I leave
tomorrow at 3:00.

12:23.076 --> 12:24.812
Phew.
I thought I missed you.

12:26.179 --> 12:27.981
I left a bunch of crap
in the Saturn

12:28.015 --> 12:29.082
and wanted
to get it back.

12:30.818 --> 12:33.586
Yeah. Here you go.

12:33.620 --> 12:36.256
Whoa. My old Kris Kross CD!
[ Chuckles ]

12:36.289 --> 12:38.058
I was getting the car
ready to sell,

12:38.091 --> 12:40.260
and that was stuck
to a Frosty lid.

12:40.293 --> 12:42.162
Wait. You're selling
the Saturn?

12:42.195 --> 12:44.331
New York's way too expensive
for a car.

12:44.364 --> 12:46.299
That's why all the cops
ride horses.

12:46.333 --> 12:47.634
I'll take the subway,
no big deal.

12:47.667 --> 12:50.770
No big deal? You're cool
with just dumping the Saturn?

12:50.804 --> 12:53.073
Who cares about all the good
times we had in there?

12:53.106 --> 12:55.175
And our Saturn talks -- I guess
those meant nothing to you.

12:55.208 --> 12:57.010
Now you're upset?

12:57.044 --> 12:58.178
You're more worked up
about the car

12:58.211 --> 12:59.646
than when I said
I was leaving!

12:59.679 --> 13:02.282
Well, to be fair,
the car isn't moving to New York

13:02.315 --> 13:04.684
and totally bailing on me
for the rest of high school!

13:04.717 --> 13:07.354
You know what? Forget it.
Have fun in New York!

13:07.387 --> 13:08.188
Peace.

13:09.857 --> 13:11.358
[ Insects chirping ]

13:11.391 --> 13:14.461
Aren't the Cascades enchanting,
family?

13:14.494 --> 13:15.662
[ Chuckles ]

13:15.695 --> 13:19.166
No, thank you.

13:19.199 --> 13:21.935
Oh, my God.
Is that Bigfoot?

13:21.969 --> 13:24.771
Emery, get the camera!

13:24.804 --> 13:26.606
Set it to burst mode!

13:26.639 --> 13:28.808
[ Scoffs ]
Then just bring it here!

13:30.510 --> 13:31.478
Louis?

13:31.511 --> 13:33.213
Oh, hey.

13:33.246 --> 13:35.815
I thought you and I
could celebrate

13:35.849 --> 13:37.317
with some champagne.

13:37.350 --> 13:41.955
I just want you to take a second
to really soak it all in.

13:41.989 --> 13:43.323
You did it.

13:43.356 --> 13:44.391
Thanks.

13:44.424 --> 13:45.725
And you deserve
some fun,

13:45.758 --> 13:47.827
so tomorrow, I'm buying
his-and-her Jet Skis

13:47.861 --> 13:50.730
so we can zip around Havasu
like a pair of dragonflies.

13:50.763 --> 13:53.033
They're not cheap,
but neither is happiness.

13:53.066 --> 13:54.902
The book is a flop,
Louis!

13:54.935 --> 13:56.436
What?

13:58.405 --> 14:01.141
[ Sighs ] It sold less than
100 copies nationwide.

14:01.174 --> 14:03.343
What about that line
at the store?

14:03.376 --> 14:06.213
Everyone was there for some
other book -- "Boy Witch."

14:06.246 --> 14:09.416
Written by a homeless
British teacher of all things.

14:09.449 --> 14:11.351
Then why did you say
it was a hit?

14:11.384 --> 14:13.720
Because between you
and the cake

14:13.753 --> 14:16.356
and Evan's big saucer eyes
going blink, blink,

14:16.389 --> 14:17.891
I didn't have a choice.

14:19.759 --> 14:22.262
I guess people just weren't
ready for your talent.

14:22.295 --> 14:25.865
But, hey, maybe your work
will be worth more when
you're dead like Monet.

14:28.768 --> 14:30.437
[ Sighs ]

14:30.470 --> 14:33.073
We'll have to cancel
the road trip.

14:33.106 --> 14:35.342
But the boys
were so excited.

14:35.375 --> 14:38.011
But can't just
fake a book tour.

14:38.045 --> 14:39.679
Everything will be fine.

14:39.712 --> 14:42.215
I'll return this tomorrow,
and then when I get back,

14:42.249 --> 14:43.783
we'll tell the boys
what happened with your book.

14:43.816 --> 14:46.086
Okay?

14:46.119 --> 14:47.754
Okay.

14:47.787 --> 14:50.123
**

14:50.157 --> 14:51.124
[ Door closes ]

14:51.158 --> 14:52.859
Good night, Havasu.

14:52.892 --> 14:54.461
**

14:54.494 --> 14:56.129
[ Birds chirping ]

14:56.163 --> 14:58.231
Morning, Ma.

14:58.265 --> 15:00.600
I'm returning the RV,
so let me know

15:00.633 --> 15:02.569
if you hid any chewing tobacco
in the seat pockets.

15:07.274 --> 15:08.241
What?!

15:08.275 --> 15:12.312
**

15:16.916 --> 15:18.418
Where's the first stop
on the book tour, Mom?

15:18.451 --> 15:19.819
Uh, Miami.

15:19.852 --> 15:21.088
But we're going north.

15:21.121 --> 15:22.622
It's a shortcut.

15:22.655 --> 15:24.791
Huh. Why couldn't we
wait for Dad?

15:24.824 --> 15:27.660
He'll join us later.
There was an emergency
at Cattleman's Ranch.

15:27.694 --> 15:29.162
What happened?!

15:29.196 --> 15:30.763
Hector's earring
fell into the chili!

15:30.797 --> 15:32.599
Let Mommy focus
on the road, please!

15:34.134 --> 15:36.169
Eddie, I was hoping
we could really dig in

15:36.203 --> 15:37.604
on your childhood today.

15:37.637 --> 15:40.207
[ Growling ] Go...away!

15:42.375 --> 15:43.676
We're gonna reschedule.
[ Pen clicks ]

15:45.212 --> 15:47.280
Hey, uh,
is Kareem here?

15:47.314 --> 15:49.016
They always ask for Kareem.

15:49.049 --> 15:50.650
He's showing
a customer an RV.

15:50.683 --> 15:53.653
Stupid question,
but what does "RV" stand for?

15:53.686 --> 15:55.322
[ Snores ]

15:55.355 --> 15:56.856
[ Quietly ]
Oh, sorry, sorry.

15:56.889 --> 15:58.858
Did my wife return
an RV this morning?

15:58.891 --> 16:00.693
20-foot ad of an Asian lady
on the side?

16:00.727 --> 16:03.096
This morning? No.

16:03.130 --> 16:04.531
Damn it.
She took our kids,

16:04.564 --> 16:06.133
and I have no idea
where they went.

16:06.166 --> 16:09.302
Well, our RVs come standard
with LoJack.

16:09.336 --> 16:10.603
I could get the tracker
and help you find them.

16:10.637 --> 16:11.938
Oh, great.
[ Chuckles ]

16:11.971 --> 16:14.141
Uh, you and Kareem, right?

16:15.342 --> 16:16.676
There it is!

16:18.745 --> 16:20.347
Another win
for Team Kareem.

16:20.380 --> 16:22.315
Kareem did it.

16:22.349 --> 16:24.151
Not the computer
inside the LoJack.

16:25.585 --> 16:26.886
[ Sighs ]

16:26.919 --> 16:28.555
That's not good.

16:28.588 --> 16:30.890
Don't worry. All the knives
are accounted for.

16:30.923 --> 16:33.826
Hey, where's your mom?

16:33.860 --> 16:35.628
Doing a reading
at the bookstore.

16:35.662 --> 16:38.031
**

16:38.065 --> 16:41.168
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar?!
Dude, Nicole is gonna flip.

16:41.201 --> 16:43.203
She has a poster of you
fighting Bruce Lee in her room.

16:45.838 --> 16:48.975
Whoa. An RV is
no place to be sad.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.577
My best friend is moving away,
and we got in a fight,

16:50.610 --> 16:52.579
but I'm cool.
I'm cool.

16:52.612 --> 16:54.047
A double "I'm cool"?

16:54.081 --> 16:56.116
Let's not gloss over this.

16:57.850 --> 17:00.153
[ Sighs ] I have three years
of high school left,

17:00.187 --> 17:02.222
and she's the only friend
who really gets me,

17:02.255 --> 17:03.656
who speaks Eddie.

17:03.690 --> 17:04.891
I take it you're Eddie?

17:06.259 --> 17:08.895
I get it.
It's hard to say goodbye.

17:08.928 --> 17:10.530
But you're making this
about you.

17:10.563 --> 17:12.765
You got to realize
that it's hard on her, too.

17:12.799 --> 17:15.068
Why?
She's the one leaving me.

17:15.102 --> 17:17.837
Look, I'm at my car lot
five days a year.

17:17.870 --> 17:20.707
When I leave,
my employees are super sad,

17:20.740 --> 17:23.776
but they're not seeing things
from where I stand at 7'2".

17:23.810 --> 17:28.348
I have to leave my best friends,
K-- Ke-- Kevin, all of them.

17:28.381 --> 17:30.083
I didn't even
think about that.

17:30.117 --> 17:32.385
Don't let your
best friend leave

17:32.419 --> 17:34.421
without knowing
she's your best friend.

17:34.454 --> 17:37.224
I get it, Kareem.
Thanks.

17:38.625 --> 17:40.527
I thought for sure that you were
gonna use a basketball metaphor.

17:40.560 --> 17:43.596
Well, you know,
I'm a man of, uh, many talents.

17:43.630 --> 17:45.532
They used to think they had me
pinned and then...

17:45.565 --> 17:47.434
skyhook.
[ Chuckles ]

17:47.467 --> 17:50.069
That's how you
break down a wall.

17:50.103 --> 17:52.439
[ Scoffs ]
He can fly now?

17:52.472 --> 17:54.407
Guess I should've
given Jennifer Hong

17:54.441 --> 17:55.942
the ability
to defy physics.

17:55.975 --> 17:57.110
Garbage.

17:59.112 --> 18:00.213
Louis: Jessica?

18:00.247 --> 18:02.882
Why'd you run off
with the boys?

18:02.915 --> 18:03.983
I stole your idea.

18:04.016 --> 18:05.218
I'm taking them
on a fake book tour.

18:05.252 --> 18:07.587
It's going well. Tomorrow
we tackle the Panhandle.

18:07.620 --> 18:10.323
Jessica,
what's going on?

18:10.357 --> 18:13.092
I don't want the boys
to find out about my book.

18:13.126 --> 18:14.961
They'll never
respect me again.

18:14.994 --> 18:16.896
[ Scoffs ]
That's ridiculous.

18:16.929 --> 18:20.600
Is it? You said yourself
they learn from watching us.

18:20.633 --> 18:23.236
If they see my book is a dud,
you know what they learn?

18:23.270 --> 18:25.138
That their mom
is a failure.

18:25.172 --> 18:29.576
**

18:29.609 --> 18:31.444
Just because
the book didn't sell

18:31.478 --> 18:34.481
doesn't mean you are a failure,
but you can't hide this.

18:34.514 --> 18:36.183
It's just as important
for the boys to see

18:36.216 --> 18:38.951
how you deal with a loss
as it is to see you succeed.

18:38.985 --> 18:42.855
It's just I've never failed
like this before in my life.

18:42.889 --> 18:45.258
I know.

18:45.292 --> 18:47.194
But I've failed
hundreds of times,

18:47.227 --> 18:48.761
and you were always there
for me.

18:48.795 --> 18:50.029
Let me be there for you.

18:51.898 --> 18:52.899
You have failed a lot.

18:55.168 --> 18:56.769
Building your own
dirt bike.

18:56.803 --> 18:58.271
Beekeeping.

18:58.305 --> 19:00.173
Cattleman's in a cup.
Yep.

19:00.207 --> 19:02.509
The banjo,
"Top Hat" Louis,

19:02.542 --> 19:03.943
forming your own
break-dance crew.

19:03.976 --> 19:05.312
Okay, let's
go tell the boys.

19:05.345 --> 19:07.046
I'm just gonna
finish this chapter.
No.

19:07.079 --> 19:09.216
Boys, your mother
has something

19:09.249 --> 19:11.351
she needs to tell you
about her book.

19:13.420 --> 19:16.856
Sometimes you forget how stupid
the rest of the world is.

19:16.889 --> 19:18.491
Like how all anybody
cares about

19:18.525 --> 19:20.793
is whether some snotty
British boy can fly and --

19:20.827 --> 19:24.063
Eddie? What's wrong?

19:24.096 --> 19:26.866
I never said goodbye
to Nicole.

19:26.899 --> 19:28.835
And she leaves
in an hour,

19:28.868 --> 19:30.903
and now we're here
on this book tour.

19:30.937 --> 19:32.372
I messed up.

19:32.405 --> 19:33.973
**

19:34.006 --> 19:35.308
Book tour is cancelled.

19:35.342 --> 19:36.943
We're going home
so Eddie can see Nicole.

19:38.245 --> 19:39.212
-Sweet!
-Yes.

19:39.246 --> 19:40.413
You're not gonna
tell them?

19:40.447 --> 19:43.350
I will later, but right now,
our son needs us.

19:43.383 --> 19:46.653
The one thing
I can't ever fail is our boys.

19:46.686 --> 19:47.987
Oh!

19:48.020 --> 19:49.522
[ Keys clatter ]
How about a heads-up?

19:49.556 --> 19:51.758
**

19:51.791 --> 19:53.125
[ Brakes hiss ]

19:54.227 --> 19:55.628
Damn it!
We're 40 minutes late!

20:00.433 --> 20:02.602
Nicole!
You're still here!

20:02.635 --> 20:03.670
I thought you
were leaving at 3:00.

20:03.703 --> 20:04.937
I'm leaving at 5:00.

20:04.971 --> 20:06.673
I told you 3:00 because

20:06.706 --> 20:08.775
it always takes you longer
than it should to come around.

20:08.808 --> 20:11.411
[ Sighs ]
You really do speak Eddie.

20:11.444 --> 20:13.280
Got time
for one last Saturn talk?

20:14.447 --> 20:15.848
I'm sorry I was a dope.

20:15.882 --> 20:18.084
I'm just...really
gonna miss you.

20:18.117 --> 20:19.752
You're going to miss me?

20:19.786 --> 20:21.354
How am I supposed
to make it without you?

20:21.388 --> 20:22.955
You had permanent shotgun.

20:22.989 --> 20:25.258
I mean, you've been there
through everything.

20:25.292 --> 20:28.060
I know it sucks we won't
be together talking like this,

20:28.094 --> 20:30.229
but you're gonna kill it
in New York.

20:30.263 --> 20:31.598
You're Nicole.
[ Chuckles ]

20:31.631 --> 20:32.932
I'm gonna miss you, girl.

20:32.965 --> 20:34.567
I'm gonna miss you, fool.

20:34.601 --> 20:37.970
**

20:38.004 --> 20:39.472
[ Sighs ]

20:39.506 --> 20:40.873
[ Sniffles ]

20:40.907 --> 20:42.609
Are you crying?

20:42.642 --> 20:44.377
Nah. It's just my allergies.
[ Chuckles ]

20:44.411 --> 20:46.713
Okay.

20:46.746 --> 20:50.550
Because you know what happens in
here stays in here, forever.

20:50.583 --> 20:51.618
Whew!

20:51.651 --> 20:53.420
It's -- It's really
flaring up now.

20:53.453 --> 20:55.121
[ Both laugh ]

20:59.292 --> 21:00.727
And with that home run,

21:00.760 --> 21:01.828
Sammy Sosa retakes the lead
over Mark McGwire.

21:01.861 --> 21:03.296
Slammin' Sammy!

21:03.330 --> 21:05.498
You know he's
on steroids, right?

21:05.532 --> 21:07.700
What steroids?

21:10.503 --> 21:12.672
Hey, I know it's going
to be difficult,

21:12.705 --> 21:13.973
but you still
need to tell the boys

21:14.006 --> 21:14.741
what happened
with the book.

21:14.774 --> 21:17.243
**

21:17.276 --> 21:18.578
What book?

21:18.611 --> 21:19.679
[ Sighs ]

21:19.712 --> 21:20.680
I know what you're doing,

21:20.713 --> 21:22.181
but you can't
just deny it happened.

21:22.214 --> 21:24.451
Deny what happened?

21:24.484 --> 21:26.486
Uh-oh.

21:34.361 --> 21:36.363
So you're the only new kid.
Big deal, right?

21:36.463 --> 21:38.898
You are gonna crush
first grade, Soph.

21:38.998 --> 21:42.569
Thanks, Dad.
A-A-And in case
you do get nervous,

21:42.669 --> 21:44.637
I got you
something special.

21:44.737 --> 21:46.906
A magical amulet.

21:47.006 --> 21:49.476
Nothing bad can happen to you
when you got this guy on.

21:49.576 --> 21:52.912
(wizard voice) Careful! Ooh,
don't let the magic out!

21:53.012 --> 21:54.581
(gasps)

21:54.681 --> 21:57.384
Did you make this
out of Post-its?

21:57.484 --> 21:58.985
No!

21:59.752 --> 22:02.154
Yes.
It's gonna be
way worse for me

22:02.254 --> 22:04.156
if I'm wearing sticky notes
around my neck.

22:04.256 --> 22:05.892
I'm good on my own.

22:05.992 --> 22:07.994
(normal voice)
You're good on your own?

22:08.094 --> 22:10.730
Yeah.
See you at pickup.

22:10.830 --> 22:11.831
Okay.

22:11.931 --> 22:14.000
Bye.
(smooches)

22:14.767 --> 22:19.506
WILL (SOFTLY):
* I've been staring
at the edge of the water *

22:19.606 --> 22:22.775
* Long as I can remember

22:22.875 --> 22:25.412
* Never really knowing why,
cha cha cha cha cha *

22:25.512 --> 22:27.580
Are you whisper-singing
"Moana" at me?

22:27.680 --> 22:29.882
Well, yeah, 'cause it always
calms you down.

22:31.017 --> 22:32.419
But not now.
Bad timing.

22:32.519 --> 22:33.620
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Come on.

22:33.720 --> 22:35.588
Read the room, right?
Okay, you got this.

22:35.688 --> 22:36.789
Bye, I love you.
-Bye.

22:36.889 --> 22:38.791
-It's gonna be fun.
-What if I miss you?

22:38.891 --> 22:39.959
Look, buddy,
we talked about this.

22:40.059 --> 22:42.294
It's only six hours.
You're gonna do great.

22:42.395 --> 22:43.696
Can I have your scarf?

22:43.796 --> 22:45.698
Graham, we're not
doing the scarf thing.

22:45.798 --> 22:48.367
Please. It helps when I have
something of yours to sniff.

22:48.468 --> 22:51.804
Look, I don't want you
sitting at your desk during
recess sniffing my stuff.

22:53.406 --> 22:56.576
Okay, fine, but you're gonna
eat vegetables tonight,

22:56.676 --> 22:57.777
the green bummer ones.

22:57.877 --> 22:59.912
(sniffs deeply)
Mmm.

23:00.012 --> 23:02.214
Like coconuts
and safety.

23:02.314 --> 23:04.283
Mom? I'm regretting
the purple.

23:04.383 --> 23:06.285
I should have dressed
like a normal kid.

23:06.385 --> 23:08.455
Hey. What's the one thing
you always have to be?

23:08.555 --> 23:09.822
-Myself?
-And who are you?

23:09.922 --> 23:11.891
Honestly, Mom,
I don't even know right now.

23:11.991 --> 23:14.461
Hey, you are a smart,
stylish young man

23:14.561 --> 23:17.329
who could pull off jewel tones
better than anyone I know.

23:17.430 --> 23:19.165
And you can cut a rug.

23:19.265 --> 23:20.467
Okay.

23:20.567 --> 23:22.101
Today, I am a grape!

23:22.201 --> 23:24.904
You heard him.
My kid's living his truth.

23:25.004 --> 23:26.739
Dad, you forgot
our lunch boxes.

23:26.839 --> 23:28.741
Okay, tell you what.

23:28.841 --> 23:32.244
Take 20 bucks and buy yourself
a burger from the grill, huh?

23:32.344 --> 23:34.447
Dad, this isn't the club.
There's no grill.

23:34.547 --> 23:36.683
Right. Here, sweetheart.
Get yourself some crap

23:36.783 --> 23:39.085
with a rainbow on it.
My kid's taking your lunch.

23:39.185 --> 23:41.488
Hey!
No one ever packed me snacks.
Make it work.

23:41.588 --> 23:43.590
Dad, you can't
call girls "sweetheart."

23:43.623 --> 23:44.857
It's not empowering.

23:44.957 --> 23:46.693
Okay, let me tell you
what is empowering --

23:46.793 --> 23:48.027
fending for yourself.

23:48.127 --> 23:50.697
Kids today,
they're treated like morons.

23:50.797 --> 23:51.831
But not you two.

23:51.931 --> 23:53.633
I would share a foxhole
with both of you,

23:53.733 --> 23:55.702
and that is the highest
compliment I can give you.

23:55.802 --> 23:57.704
All right, hit me
with the family motto.

23:57.804 --> 24:00.106
No weakness.
Drain the swamp.

24:00.206 --> 24:01.207
(all exhale sharply)

24:01.307 --> 24:02.975
Excuse me. Sir?
Are you supposed to be here?

24:03.075 --> 24:05.277
Do you have a child
in this class?

24:05.377 --> 24:07.279
Oh, uh,
he's my neighbor.

24:07.379 --> 24:10.116
He's 20,
and he's raising a baby alone.

24:10.216 --> 24:11.217
He hasn't fully accepted

24:11.317 --> 24:12.852
that his life has changed
forever, you know?

24:12.952 --> 24:14.987
Yeah, um, I'm not
running a support group.

24:15.087 --> 24:17.123
You're a little mean.
I like it.

24:17.223 --> 24:18.958
(Jack cries)
Where am I?

24:19.058 --> 24:21.360
Oh, I had
the strangest dream.

24:21.460 --> 24:22.629
(Jack cooing)

24:24.196 --> 24:25.131
Oh.

24:25.231 --> 24:27.066
Sir, I'm gonna
ask you to leave.

24:27.166 --> 24:28.234
He goes where we go.

24:28.334 --> 24:30.402
Here you go.
Get yourself something nice.

24:30.503 --> 24:31.704
I can't accept tips.

24:31.804 --> 24:34.541
Okay. It, uh,
"dropped on the floor."

24:34.641 --> 24:35.908
(Ringing)

24:36.008 --> 24:38.477
Attention! Excuse me!

24:38.578 --> 24:40.847
Hello, hi!
Quiet coyotes.

24:40.947 --> 24:43.349
Quiet coyotes.
Thank you.

24:43.449 --> 24:45.184
My name is Will Cooper,

24:45.284 --> 24:48.655
and I have the honor
of being your Room Parent.

24:48.755 --> 24:50.489
-Nice.
-That's exciting.

24:50.590 --> 24:51.924
-Oh, no.
-Ooh, this is bad.

24:52.024 --> 24:54.493
Is he wearing a necklace
made of garbage?

24:54.594 --> 24:56.996
Uh, Sophie and I
are new to the school,

24:57.096 --> 24:58.497
and we are so looking forward

24:58.598 --> 25:00.900
to getting to know
every one of you.

25:01.000 --> 25:03.435
I am single.

25:03.536 --> 25:04.503
Um...

25:04.604 --> 25:06.038
Always try to
get that out there.

25:06.138 --> 25:07.774
Just never quite sure
how to work it in.

25:07.874 --> 25:10.276
But that just means
I have more time

25:10.376 --> 25:12.945
for creating a little
hot lunch option I call...

25:13.045 --> 25:14.847
(Oprah-style singsong voice)
..."Taco Tuesday," y'all!

25:14.947 --> 25:16.616
(Applause)
(Normal voice) Right?

25:16.716 --> 25:17.750
Did he just
"Oprah" that?

25:17.850 --> 25:19.018
He know he's white,
right?

25:19.118 --> 25:20.086
Everybody knows.

25:20.186 --> 25:21.453
Come on! Give me fives!
All right!

25:21.554 --> 25:22.755
Somebody tell me
when it's safe

25:22.855 --> 25:24.724
for my nuts
to return to my body.

25:24.824 --> 25:26.192
Now, I see a lot of you
are wondering,

25:26.292 --> 25:27.894
"Where do I fit
into the equation?"

25:27.994 --> 25:33.365
Five words -- "One hundred
percent parent participation."

25:33.465 --> 25:35.134
He's got to be kidding.
(Murmuring)

25:35.234 --> 25:36.969
-I am not kidding.
-Not happening.

25:37.069 --> 25:39.371
I'm gonna be standing
right outside that door

25:39.471 --> 25:41.373
with this sign-up sheet, okay?

25:41.473 --> 25:43.810
This is what's become
of the American male.

25:43.910 --> 25:45.477
We used to make things.

25:45.578 --> 25:47.980
Empathy, Douglas.
He's single. We're single.

25:48.080 --> 25:49.649
No, I've never been
that single.

25:49.749 --> 25:51.250
Do not try to avoid me,

25:51.350 --> 25:53.653
'cause I will hunt you down
and circle you like a shark.

25:53.753 --> 25:54.954
(imitating shark)
(children gasp)

25:55.054 --> 26:00.159
**

26:00.259 --> 26:02.061
Okay, guys,
we need to talk babysitting.

26:02.161 --> 26:03.162
I'll need help
Thursday because

26:03.262 --> 26:05.097
all the paralegals
are going out to karaoke.

26:05.197 --> 26:07.233
Just kidding.
We're staying late to file.

26:07.333 --> 26:08.334
On Thursday, I'm busy.

26:08.434 --> 26:09.669
I got to 'Gram
my new Yeezys.

26:09.769 --> 26:11.904
You're a ridiculous person.
Thanks, man!

26:12.004 --> 26:13.239
Well, at least
he doesn't eat steak

26:13.339 --> 26:15.274
with the same pasty old
white guys night after night.

26:15.374 --> 26:16.909
We're not
pasty old white guys.

26:17.009 --> 26:18.110
We're dermatologists

26:18.210 --> 26:20.179
saving the lives
of pasty old white guys.

26:20.279 --> 26:22.248
Hey, guys,
I need some help.

26:22.348 --> 26:24.250
Found this
in Graham's backpack.

26:24.350 --> 26:26.085
Aww, Graham
wrote a love letter.

26:26.185 --> 26:27.253
Aww.

26:27.353 --> 26:28.287
-Oh, no, to Zoe?
-Yes.

26:28.387 --> 26:29.588
That girl who always
wears bunny ears?

26:29.689 --> 26:30.923
-She's crazy.
-She runs the school.

26:31.023 --> 26:32.191
And if she
breaks Graham's heart,

26:32.291 --> 26:34.593
I will chop off her feet
and turn them into keychains.

26:34.694 --> 26:36.362
-Huh?
-Just kidding.

26:36.462 --> 26:38.197
But I'll be really mad.
(indistinct talking
in distance)

26:38.297 --> 26:39.632
Oh, God, the new guy.

26:39.732 --> 26:41.868
...field trips? Actually,
are you insured drivers?

26:41.968 --> 26:43.936
We have got to deal
with him.

26:44.036 --> 26:46.605
But I have no time to be
handing out tacos all year.
No.

26:46.706 --> 26:48.174
Word.
I'm still in awe of how you
did away

26:48.274 --> 26:49.842
with last year's
Room Parent.

26:49.942 --> 26:52.111
You wiped all trace of us from
that phone tree.
It's kind
of my thing.

26:52.211 --> 26:54.446
Parents! Will Cooper!

26:54.546 --> 26:55.948
I just wanted to,
uh, circle back

26:56.048 --> 26:58.484
and see where we are
vis-Ã -vis committees.

26:58.584 --> 26:59.886
You know what?
Let me say it plain --

26:59.986 --> 27:01.988
we're not gonna do anything
you want us to do.

27:02.088 --> 27:03.555
No, man.
We're single parents.

27:03.656 --> 27:05.524
We don't volunteer.
We just try and survive

27:05.624 --> 27:07.960
until a time in the day when
it's appropriate to open wine.

27:08.060 --> 27:10.462
I don't know if you
heard my announcement,
but I'm single, as well.

27:10.562 --> 27:11.798
-We heard.
-We -- We heard.
-We heard, bro.

27:11.898 --> 27:13.733
So I have no wiggle room
on parent participation.

27:13.833 --> 27:16.202
You're in deep,
aren't you?

27:16.302 --> 27:17.804
Deep in what?

27:17.904 --> 27:19.405
The vortex.

27:19.505 --> 27:21.874
That place where you're
so wrapped up in your kid

27:21.974 --> 27:24.243
that you've lost all touch
with your adult life

27:24.343 --> 27:25.745
and the person
you used to be.

27:25.845 --> 27:29.415
I know,
'cause I've been there.

27:29.515 --> 27:32.151
* The wheels on the bus
go round and round *
(baby crying)

27:32.251 --> 27:34.520
* Round and round,
round and round *

27:34.620 --> 27:37.423
* The wheels on the bus
go round and round *

27:37.523 --> 27:38.390
(thud)

27:38.490 --> 27:39.859
It happens
to all of us.

27:39.959 --> 27:41.427
But (chuckles) I don't think
I'm in a vortex.

27:41.527 --> 27:44.697
Will, when was the last time
you stayed up past 10:00?

27:44.797 --> 27:45.865
In the nighttime?

27:45.965 --> 27:47.533
Okay, when's the last time
you made love?

27:47.633 --> 27:48.534
(laughing) Oh, my...

27:48.634 --> 27:50.202
It's okay.
There's no judgment here.

27:50.302 --> 27:51.537
This is a safe space.

27:51.637 --> 27:53.372
For real.
Yeah, just tell us.
Just ballpark.

27:53.472 --> 27:56.575
All right, ballpark...

27:56.675 --> 27:59.211
give or take a month,
it's been about...

27:59.311 --> 28:00.446
five years.

28:00.546 --> 28:01.714
-Oh, baby, no.
-Whoo!

28:01.814 --> 28:02.715
(indistinct shouting)

28:02.815 --> 28:03.850
-Dang!
-Oh, my God.

28:03.950 --> 28:05.584
You guys said that
this was a safe space.

28:05.684 --> 28:06.618
Not that safe.

28:06.719 --> 28:09.288
You know, what you need
is a date.

28:09.388 --> 28:10.356
Poppy?

28:10.456 --> 28:11.858
There. I made you
a Tinder account.

28:11.958 --> 28:14.060
How did you -- Is that my face
on Putin's body?

28:14.160 --> 28:15.527
Pushing you into
the deep end, Will.

28:15.627 --> 28:17.096
That's how we do this.

28:17.196 --> 28:19.131
If I'm being honest,
the timing's not great.

28:19.231 --> 28:20.699
It's 120 days
till Christmas --

28:20.800 --> 28:22.634
Are you gonna hide
behind that sign-up sheet

28:22.735 --> 28:24.036
or am I swiping right?

28:24.136 --> 28:25.537
I've got Room Parent
responsibilities --

28:25.637 --> 28:27.206
Swipe! Swipe!
I have no investment
either way.

28:27.306 --> 28:30.076
I've never done something
like this before, okay?
(chanting "Swipe!")

28:30.176 --> 28:33.212
You know what? Do it.
Swipe left!

28:33.312 --> 28:34.546
It's "swipe right."

28:34.646 --> 28:36.916
It's "swipe right,"
and you just said that. Sorry.

28:41.087 --> 28:43.389
Okay, okay, okay.
We got Emma, we got Amy,

28:43.489 --> 28:45.457
we got Rory, we got Graham.
Who are you?

28:45.557 --> 28:47.459
Wrong van, kid.
Get out of here. Beat it.

28:47.559 --> 28:50.596
Angie! Hey!
Will Cooper from yesterday.

28:50.696 --> 28:52.264
So, tonight's date night.
-Ooh.

28:52.364 --> 28:54.000
Remember, a real man
pays for dinner.

28:54.100 --> 28:56.468
Is that true? I mean, I don't
know by 2018's standards --

28:56.602 --> 28:58.237
Will, I say this
with an open heart

28:58.337 --> 28:59.738
and nothing but love --

28:59.839 --> 29:01.240
you're a disaster.
-Preach.

29:01.340 --> 29:03.242
Yeah, I don't know
if I'm a disaster.

29:03.342 --> 29:04.977
I mean, yes,
I'm experiencing some anxiety,

29:05.077 --> 29:06.745
but that's normal, okay?
And I'm just --

29:06.846 --> 29:08.280
Will. I don't have time
for this.

29:08.380 --> 29:09.515
-Oh.
-We got you the date,

29:09.615 --> 29:11.450
and now I have to babysit
everyone else's kids

29:11.550 --> 29:13.585
so I can have a Saturday night
to drink champagne out of a can

29:13.685 --> 29:15.354
and watch
a bird documentary.

29:15.454 --> 29:16.823
Okay, 'cause I was actually
coming over to say

29:16.923 --> 29:17.924
I could babysit today
if you wa--

29:18.024 --> 29:20.526
-We'll be there in 15 minutes.
-Oh, cool.

29:20.626 --> 29:21.627
* That's right
DIEGO: Yo, why did

29:21.727 --> 29:22.995
you bring your baby
to the sneaker line?

29:23.095 --> 29:25.131
'Cause free babysitting doesn't
just fall out of the sky.

29:25.231 --> 29:26.933
(scoffs)
(cellphone chimes)

29:27.033 --> 29:28.868
Oh, snap!
Free babysitting!

29:28.968 --> 29:30.436
All right, yo, hey.
Be right back.

29:30.536 --> 29:31.470
Wait --
Okay.

29:31.570 --> 29:32.704
I -- Imma come back.
Hold my spot.

29:32.805 --> 29:34.373
I -- I'll be back
without the baby. Just me.

29:34.473 --> 29:35.541
Hold my spot!

29:35.641 --> 29:36.843
**

29:36.943 --> 29:39.311
(doorbell rings)
Welcome, dudes! Will Cooper!

29:39.411 --> 29:41.347
Do you guys want to go
play in my room?

29:41.447 --> 29:43.182
The theme is
"tasteful unicorn."

29:43.282 --> 29:45.617
Thanks a lot. We'll be back
in a few. Good God.

29:45.717 --> 29:48.320
-This place is a wonderland.
-Every chair is a beanbag.

29:48.420 --> 29:50.656
There's no chair
that isn't a beanbag.

29:50.756 --> 29:53.125
All chairs
currently have beans.

29:53.225 --> 29:54.393
Indoor trampoline?

29:54.493 --> 29:55.962
So they can bounce
when it's raining.

29:56.062 --> 29:58.364
(door closes)
Will, sit down.

29:59.298 --> 30:00.699
(thud)

30:00.799 --> 30:03.069
What are you gonna wear
on your date tonight?

30:03.169 --> 30:04.636
-This?
-Oh, God.

30:04.736 --> 30:06.338
(chuckles)
Oh, you're serious.

30:06.438 --> 30:07.406
Or -- Or...

30:07.506 --> 30:09.708
(Zipping)
...I do have another option.

30:09.808 --> 30:10.910
Ah!

30:11.010 --> 30:12.044
Shorts!
(Jack cries)

30:12.144 --> 30:14.013
Y-Your pants are making
my baby cry, man!

30:14.113 --> 30:16.015
Make it stop.
Make it all stop.

30:16.115 --> 30:17.749
Here. Oh.
I know. I know.

30:17.850 --> 30:20.486
Rock, squat, pause.

30:20.586 --> 30:21.988
Rock, squat, pause.

30:22.088 --> 30:23.322
(crying stops)
Oh. There we go.

30:23.422 --> 30:25.824
Oh, my God.
What did you do?

30:25.925 --> 30:26.893
It's a little something
I call

30:26.993 --> 30:28.727
rock, squat, pause.

30:28.827 --> 30:29.862
-"Puss"?
-No.

30:29.962 --> 30:30.829
-"Puzz."
-Rock, squat --

30:30.930 --> 30:33.032
Listen --
rock, squat, pause.

30:33.132 --> 30:34.934
-Puh...
-"Pause." "Pause."

30:35.034 --> 30:35.834
Oh, "pause"!

30:35.935 --> 30:36.835
Say it with me.
Ro--

30:36.936 --> 30:38.504
-Never.
-Nah, man.

30:38.604 --> 30:39.605
What if I learn
to do that

30:39.705 --> 30:41.207
and then I haven't had sex
in five years

30:41.307 --> 30:43.609
and I'm wearing pants
that zip off into shorts?

30:43.709 --> 30:45.611
Give me my baby.
(Jack coos)

30:45.711 --> 30:47.279
Ah, you guys,
you're right.

30:47.379 --> 30:49.115
I-I -- I'm clearly
not ready, okay?

30:49.215 --> 30:51.183
I-I say we put the brakes
on the date tonight,

30:51.283 --> 30:53.285
okay, just until after
Taco Tuesday's figured out.

30:53.385 --> 30:55.787
I want to keep that guac
from browning --

30:55.888 --> 30:57.256
No. No. Focus.

30:57.356 --> 30:59.458
There's honestly a lot of fear
that's creeping in.

30:59.558 --> 31:01.060
-Take a deep breath.
-(exhales sharply)

31:01.160 --> 31:02.194
You're going on this date.

31:02.294 --> 31:04.463
(unsure) Good.
I'm excited about that.

31:04.563 --> 31:05.898
DOUGLAS: Hey,
so just making sure,

31:05.998 --> 31:08.034
you're gonna be taking
Emma and Amy tonight?

31:08.134 --> 31:10.869
Because I'm getting together
with my dermatologist pals.

31:10.970 --> 31:12.738
Oh, Rory wanted me
to ask you to come

31:12.838 --> 31:14.706
to his dance party
tonight.

31:14.806 --> 31:16.575
Aww, what a sweetheart.
Pass.

31:16.675 --> 31:18.477
I told you,
he's going through a thing.

31:18.577 --> 31:20.746
He won't even wear his favorite
leotard to school

31:20.846 --> 31:22.581
'cause he's scared other kids
will make fun of him.

31:22.681 --> 31:23.950
Well, of course they're
gonna make fun of him.

31:24.050 --> 31:25.117
When I was a boy,

31:25.217 --> 31:27.486
I got beaten up for smiling
at a basketball game.

31:27.586 --> 31:28.887
All right, look.
I don't know why,

31:28.988 --> 31:29.922
but my kid likes you.

31:30.022 --> 31:31.657
Okay? And in case
you haven't noticed,

31:31.757 --> 31:33.325
he doesn't have another man
in his life,

31:33.425 --> 31:35.227
so why don't you just
show up for him?

31:35.327 --> 31:38.264
I don't dance, okay,
especially with guys.

31:38.364 --> 31:41.000
You know, I still can't
wrap my head around this place.

31:41.100 --> 31:43.169
Why does every book have to be
on yoga and menopause?

31:43.269 --> 31:47.239
Douglas...
you are why we march.

31:47.339 --> 31:48.975
Oh, God.

31:49.075 --> 31:50.576
Yo, why do we
have to do this again?

31:50.676 --> 31:53.479
I just don't want to send him
out into the world like this.

31:53.579 --> 31:55.014
I mean,
it would be a crime.

31:55.114 --> 31:56.748
It's like leaving a baby
on a doorstep

31:56.848 --> 31:58.117
and hoping for the best.

32:00.119 --> 32:01.187
Miggy.
Hmm?

32:01.287 --> 32:02.354
You can't actually
do that.

32:02.454 --> 32:04.190
-(scoffs) I knew that.
-Just checking.

32:04.290 --> 32:06.592
I just don't want him
to bomb his date

32:06.692 --> 32:09.195
and start harassing us again
about hot lunch.

32:09.295 --> 32:12.364
This is the third pair
of earmuffs I have found.

32:12.464 --> 32:14.200
Who hurt this guy?

32:14.300 --> 32:18.204
"Zoe, I want to hug you
and give you all my gum."

32:18.304 --> 32:20.039
That's a great start.

32:20.139 --> 32:23.175
I've been in love with Zoe
since day one of kindergarten.

32:23.275 --> 32:25.111
Then she put those
bunny ears on --

32:25.211 --> 32:26.945
stick a fork in me,
I'm done.

32:27.046 --> 32:28.114
-It's your first love.
-(slurps)

32:28.214 --> 32:29.715
That's a big deal.
It's exciting.

32:29.815 --> 32:31.717
You shouldn't be afraid
to let your feelings out.

32:31.817 --> 32:32.784
Exactly.

32:32.884 --> 32:34.953
That's how I want to play it
with Zoe.

32:35.054 --> 32:37.223
Raw, open, positive.

32:37.323 --> 32:38.390
Oh, by the way,

32:38.490 --> 32:40.492
don't let my mom scare you
about the date tonight.

32:40.592 --> 32:42.861
She doesn't
believe in love because...

32:42.961 --> 32:44.796
my dad is kind of
a garbage human.

32:44.896 --> 32:47.033
That's good to know.

32:47.133 --> 32:49.635
But I'm gonna cut you off
on the juice boxes, 'kay, bud?

32:49.735 --> 32:52.671
Hey, Will? Angie says
I have to give you a makeover.

32:53.672 --> 32:55.841
(sighs)
This is my Everest.

32:55.941 --> 32:58.244
ANGIE: (in distance)
Oh, my God!

32:58.344 --> 33:00.679
**

33:00.779 --> 33:02.581
Angie, are you hurt?

33:02.681 --> 33:04.083
Why do you have this?

33:04.183 --> 33:05.217
Oh. (scoffs)

33:05.317 --> 33:07.153
Honestly, I've never
seen that before in my life.

33:07.253 --> 33:10.189
Dude, your wallet
is in here

33:10.289 --> 33:12.658
and a bag of popcorn
that's still hot.

33:12.758 --> 33:14.326
You've used this today.

33:14.426 --> 33:15.827
Yeah, I use it
for snacks, okay?

33:15.927 --> 33:17.996
Nobody ever tells dads
what to do about snacks,

33:18.097 --> 33:20.532
and this is a good
snack holder.

33:20.632 --> 33:26.238
It was actually my wife's...
before she left.

33:27.106 --> 33:30.542
Oh. I'm sorry.

33:30.642 --> 33:33.279
Do you think that
maybe there's a reason --

33:33.379 --> 33:34.713
I don't know, just
throwing it out there --

33:34.813 --> 33:39.918
that this is the bag
she didn't take when she left?

33:40.018 --> 33:41.520
(both laugh)

33:43.122 --> 33:44.756
Do you miss her?

33:44.856 --> 33:46.392
No.

33:46.492 --> 33:48.260
But I miss having someone,

33:48.360 --> 33:51.530
and not just for the bad stuff
or hard stuff or whatever,

33:51.630 --> 33:53.632
but -- but for
all of the good things,

33:53.732 --> 33:55.867
like when she
lost her first tooth

33:55.967 --> 33:57.636
and when she
told her first joke

33:57.736 --> 34:00.072
and the week she
demanded I call her

34:00.172 --> 34:01.607
"Jelly Bean
Teen Machine."

34:02.408 --> 34:05.711
Nobody tells you
how lonely it can be.

34:05.811 --> 34:09.815
One time, I made a boyfriend
out of a pile of laundry...

34:09.915 --> 34:11.250
and I rolled around
in him.

34:11.350 --> 34:12.384
(chuckles)

34:12.484 --> 34:13.752
It wasn't built to last.

34:13.852 --> 34:16.122
(both laugh)

34:16.222 --> 34:19.825
But when you have kids,
something happens to you.

34:19.925 --> 34:21.160
You become mush.
Mm.

34:21.260 --> 34:23.229
But you got to hide that.
That's what I tell Graham.

34:23.329 --> 34:26.165
Otherwise, that little weirdo's
gonna get his heart broken.

34:26.265 --> 34:27.399
I-I honestly don't know

34:27.499 --> 34:30.569
if I'm capable
of hiding my mush.

34:30.669 --> 34:31.770
I mean,
you guys are lucky.

34:31.870 --> 34:33.339
You have each other
to look out for one another,

34:33.439 --> 34:36.242
but it's just me.

34:36.342 --> 34:38.244
Do you ever
look at each other and go,

34:38.344 --> 34:41.079
"Ah, it takes a vill--"
Don't say it.

34:41.180 --> 34:42.281
Just throw out
the bag.

34:42.381 --> 34:45.584
Hey. Did Angie
text you her plan?

34:45.684 --> 34:47.119
Yeah, we help him
get ready for the date,

34:47.219 --> 34:49.288
and then we never
have to volunteer.

34:49.388 --> 34:50.589
Hello, ladies.

34:50.622 --> 34:52.158
-Hi, Dad.
-Hey, Dad.

34:52.258 --> 34:54.526
-Hey, girls. What are you doing?
-Will's floor mats.

34:54.626 --> 34:56.962
Would it kill him to shampoo
them once in a while?

34:57.062 --> 34:59.030
People don't think
that kids can buff and wax,

34:59.131 --> 35:00.532
but they're
the perfect height.

35:00.632 --> 35:04.136
Before I can commit to a blazer,
ask yourself --

35:04.236 --> 35:05.804
can this man pull off
this vest?

35:05.904 --> 35:07.105
I mean, he doesn't
have the arms,

35:07.206 --> 35:08.707
but, you know,
he might have the attitude.

35:08.807 --> 35:09.941
-No, no vest.
-Vest.

35:10.041 --> 35:11.943
-For the love of God, no vest.
-Mm-hmm. Vest.

35:12.043 --> 35:15.514
Maybe this
wants to live here,

35:15.614 --> 35:18.116
for tonight's dance party?
-I'm seeing it.

35:18.217 --> 35:19.785
-* Dance party
-Oh, okay, please.

35:19.885 --> 35:21.720
Forget it. We've been trying
to get him

35:21.820 --> 35:23.121
to sing and dance
for years.

35:23.222 --> 35:24.956
They're right.
I-I'm sorry, kid,

35:25.056 --> 35:26.358
but I'm not
going to the party.

35:26.458 --> 35:29.995
That's okay.
Maybe next time.

35:30.095 --> 35:31.230
(birds chirping)

35:31.330 --> 35:32.731
Nice, Douglas.
Real nice.

35:32.831 --> 35:34.300
Rory, I'll wear your vest.
-What?

35:34.400 --> 35:36.235
You don't have the right torso
for a vest, Mom.

35:36.335 --> 35:37.969
Stop trying
to make it happen.

35:38.069 --> 35:39.671
-Ah, I get it, Doug.
-Douglas.

35:39.771 --> 35:42.040
Afraid to risk
embarrassing yourself,

35:42.140 --> 35:43.709
but that's the greatest part
of parenting is,

35:43.809 --> 35:45.577
it gets you
out of your comfort zone.

35:45.677 --> 35:48.214
Look, I'm not interested
in leaving my comfort zone,

35:48.314 --> 35:49.915
and I haven't been
since my wife died.

35:50.015 --> 35:51.550
Oh, I'm --
No, no, I see
you want to hug me,

35:51.650 --> 35:53.652
and I'm gonna have to
stop you right there.

35:53.752 --> 35:55.521
I can't imagine
losing your best friend.

35:55.621 --> 35:57.856
She was a 26-year-old
exotic dancer.

35:57.956 --> 35:58.990
She looked great
in pants.

35:59.090 --> 36:00.492
Ain't love
a funny thing.

36:00.592 --> 36:02.494
Anyway, I said,
"Okay, I'll have kids,"

36:02.594 --> 36:04.095
thinking I would change
one diaper

36:04.196 --> 36:06.665
and get dementia right before
they hit their teens.

36:06.765 --> 36:09.501
Instead, she dropped dead
and left me with two baby girls.

36:09.601 --> 36:12.871
The point is, I don't need
any more surprises.

36:12.971 --> 36:16.608
All right, but it's never
too late to try something new.

36:16.708 --> 36:18.109
I think it'd be
good for you, Doug.

36:18.210 --> 36:20.512
Douglas.
I think it'd be good
for your girls.

36:20.612 --> 36:22.848
You don't have to
go it alone.

36:22.948 --> 36:24.383
I can be your friend,
Doug.

36:24.483 --> 36:26.017
Douglas.
It's Douglas.

36:26.117 --> 36:27.853
And I don't need
any more friends.

36:27.953 --> 36:29.755
The only reason
why any of us are here

36:29.855 --> 36:31.390
is so we can
get out of volunteering.

36:31.490 --> 36:32.624
Wait, hold on.

36:32.724 --> 36:35.394
Angie, is that true?

36:35.494 --> 36:36.562
Look...
(sighs)

36:36.662 --> 36:39.130
I told you about
Jelly Bean Teen Machine.

36:39.231 --> 36:41.367
Wait.
We wanted to help you.

36:41.467 --> 36:44.536
I mean, we do now.
-No, it's fine, honestly.

36:44.636 --> 36:47.205
We're not friends,
which is actually a good thing,

36:47.306 --> 36:49.908
'cause now I can admit I didn't
throw away the mermaid bag.

36:50.008 --> 36:54.646
I hid it in the petticoat
of Barbie B. Anthony!

36:55.447 --> 36:56.882
DOUGLAS: A man
with a mermaid bag.

36:56.982 --> 36:57.916
I blame Obama.

36:58.016 --> 37:00.319
I don't know
how to cover up my mush.

37:00.419 --> 37:01.753
But maybe
that's not a bad thing.

37:01.853 --> 37:04.590
Maybe you guys could actually
use a little bit more mush.

37:04.690 --> 37:06.558
Will, I will
hand out tacos.

37:06.658 --> 37:08.927
No. Don't, okay?

37:09.027 --> 37:10.662
It's just disappointing.

37:10.762 --> 37:11.797
I thought I'd finally
found

37:11.897 --> 37:13.932
a group
that I could share this with.

37:14.032 --> 37:15.834
It takes a vill--
-Don't say it.

37:15.934 --> 37:17.102
It takes a vill--

37:17.202 --> 37:18.136
-Stop!
-No, no.

37:18.236 --> 37:19.838
Well, thanks
for getting me a date,

37:19.938 --> 37:21.072
which I now have to go on.

37:21.172 --> 37:25.110
Sophie, I'm taking you
to Nana's.

37:25.210 --> 37:27.279
It takes a village.
Ha, I did it.

37:30.449 --> 37:32.250
Dang, girl.
I just love you.

37:32.351 --> 37:34.152
I love you, too, honey.

37:34.252 --> 37:35.854
And also you told me
five minutes ago.

37:35.954 --> 37:39.024
No, I was reading over
an e-mail to Zoe.

37:39.124 --> 37:40.959
I think it's good.
Send.

37:41.059 --> 37:42.461
(whoosh)
What? You sent?

37:42.561 --> 37:44.195
You got to put yourself
out there.

37:44.296 --> 37:47.866
Will gets it.
He told me to go for it.

37:47.966 --> 37:49.701
That was
a really fun dinner.

37:49.801 --> 37:51.102
I loved when you looked up
from your phone.

37:51.202 --> 37:53.038
But it is good that you got to
FaceTime with your sister.

37:53.138 --> 37:54.873
You guys worked through
so many issues.

37:54.973 --> 37:55.841
(door slams)

37:55.941 --> 37:57.208
Should we make out now?

37:57.309 --> 37:58.276
Gah.

37:58.377 --> 37:59.345
**

37:59.445 --> 38:01.347
Mwah. Mwah. Oh, wow,
this is happening.

38:01.447 --> 38:03.382
-Take your pants off.
-Get these jeans down.

38:03.482 --> 38:05.651
There we go. Okay.

38:05.751 --> 38:06.852
Oh.

38:06.952 --> 38:08.286
Oh,
the touch of a woman.

38:08.387 --> 38:11.022
(exhales sharply)
I love you.

38:13.291 --> 38:14.326
You what?

38:14.426 --> 38:15.827
(door slams)

38:15.927 --> 38:18.497
Good night.

38:18.597 --> 38:20.198
(sighs)

38:21.800 --> 38:23.301
Oh, my keys.

38:23.402 --> 38:26.405
(knocks on door)
Heather, please open the door.
Please let me in.

38:26.505 --> 38:28.640
(pounding on door)
I need to come
into your apartment.

38:28.740 --> 38:29.708
I'm just a dad who says

38:29.808 --> 38:31.577
"I love you"
a thousand times a day,

38:31.677 --> 38:33.879
and that's not a bad thing.

38:33.979 --> 38:36.582
Hi, are you in there?
I don't love you.

38:36.682 --> 38:38.817
I'm not even sure I like you.

38:38.917 --> 38:39.985
My keys are inside!

38:40.085 --> 38:41.720
(cellphone rings)
Heather -- Will Cooper.

38:41.820 --> 38:44.556
How could you tell Graham
to put himself out there?

38:44.656 --> 38:47.926
He's gonna get hurt.
Wait, why are you answering?

38:48.026 --> 38:49.695
Aren't you supposed to
be on a date?

38:49.795 --> 38:50.996
Well, I let out my mush,

38:51.096 --> 38:54.032
and now there's mush
all over this lady's apartment,

38:54.132 --> 38:56.034
and my keys
are locked inside.

38:56.134 --> 38:57.436
You guys were right.
I can't do this.

38:57.536 --> 38:59.204
(siren wails in distance)
But maybe that's a good thing,

38:59.304 --> 39:00.939
because I actually like
being single.

39:01.039 --> 39:02.574
It's gonna give me
more time to figure out

39:02.674 --> 39:03.909
Sophie's Halloween costume.

39:04.009 --> 39:04.943
She's going as a princess,

39:05.043 --> 39:06.445
but I have to find
my own spin on that.

39:06.545 --> 39:07.513
Uh, are those sirens?

39:07.613 --> 39:08.780
Yeah, but they're not for me.

39:08.880 --> 39:10.449
-Sir, don't move.
-Oh, they are for me.

39:10.549 --> 39:12.050
Oh -- Oh, my God.
Will. Will --

39:12.150 --> 39:13.351
-Hello, officers.
-Will, what's going on?

39:13.452 --> 39:14.386
Will Cooper.

39:14.486 --> 39:15.687
* That's right, hold it down

39:15.787 --> 39:18.790
(Jack coos)
Miggy! Emergency! Get in!

39:18.890 --> 39:22.193
Dude, tell your weird
parent friends to stay away.

39:22.293 --> 39:24.262
We got to earn respect
on the sneaker line.

39:24.362 --> 39:25.864
(Jack coos)

39:25.964 --> 39:27.566
(indistinct conversations)

39:27.666 --> 39:31.302
**

39:31.403 --> 39:34.039
So I cut off
the skin tag on the green,

39:34.139 --> 39:36.307
and I still managed
to make a birdie.

39:36.408 --> 39:38.444
(laughter)
Douglas.

39:38.544 --> 39:39.778
Will's in trouble.
We got to go.

39:39.878 --> 39:41.813
What, I-I --
I'm the only
babysitter you got,

39:41.913 --> 39:44.115
and I'm not afraid
to go on strike.

39:44.215 --> 39:46.818
**

39:46.918 --> 39:48.654
My ex, she's in the Sudan.

39:48.754 --> 39:50.656
She's a human-rights lawyer.
She's doing great work,

39:50.756 --> 39:52.424
and -- and, you know,
I don't fault her for that.

39:52.524 --> 39:55.994
I just -- I-I never imagined
raising a child on my own,

39:56.094 --> 40:01.066
and I think part of me still
feels like she's coming back.

40:01.166 --> 40:04.269
Dude,
she's not coming back.

40:04.369 --> 40:06.404
**

40:06.505 --> 40:10.408
We all got left,
but we're not alone.

40:10.509 --> 40:11.577
(gate closes)

40:11.677 --> 40:13.912
Officers, let him go.
He's not dangerous.

40:14.012 --> 40:15.313
Look at his shoes.
He's wearing Keds.

40:15.413 --> 40:17.082
OFFICER: His Keds
are not the issue, ma'am.

40:17.182 --> 40:18.249
But they are an issue.

40:18.349 --> 40:19.585
Look,
he didn't hurt anyone.

40:19.685 --> 40:21.352
Let's forget about this,
officers.

40:21.453 --> 40:23.254
Go ahead.
Get yourself something nice.

40:23.354 --> 40:24.322
I know what you make.

40:24.422 --> 40:26.157
Sir, put the money away.
You, come with us.

40:26.257 --> 40:28.159
(cellphone ringing)
I -- I'm so sorry.

40:29.160 --> 40:31.029
Sophie, hey.

40:31.129 --> 40:37.035
Dad, I know I said I didn't
need the song anymore, but...

40:37.135 --> 40:39.437
Of course.

40:40.806 --> 40:45.611
* I've been staring
at the edge of the water *

40:45.711 --> 40:48.313
* Long as I can remember

40:48.413 --> 40:52.651
* Never really knowing why

40:52.751 --> 40:58.456
* I wish I could
be the perfect daughter *

40:58.557 --> 41:01.126
* But I go back to the water

41:01.226 --> 41:05.631
* No matter how hard I try

41:05.731 --> 41:08.800
BOTH: * See the line
where the sky meets the sea *

41:08.900 --> 41:11.069
* It calls me

41:11.169 --> 41:14.573
* And no one knows

41:14.673 --> 41:17.242
* How far it goes

41:17.342 --> 41:19.344
EMMA: I knew it.

41:19.444 --> 41:21.379
-* What's beyond that line?
Will I cross that line? *
-He knows all the words.

41:21.479 --> 41:24.415
-* The line where
the sky meets the sea *
-That beautiful bastard.

41:24.516 --> 41:27.152
WILL: * It calls me

41:27.252 --> 41:30.321
* And no one knows
-Rory, would you like to dance?

41:30.421 --> 41:33.491
-* How far it goes
-The answer is always yes.

41:33.592 --> 41:38.496
-* If the wind in my sail
on the sea stays behind me *
-Hey.

41:38.597 --> 41:41.166
-* One day I'll know
-You're looking so good, Rory!

41:41.266 --> 41:42.500
* How far I'll go

41:42.601 --> 41:45.837
-Whoo! Go, baby!
-Whoo-hoo!

41:45.937 --> 41:48.173
(vocalizing)

41:48.273 --> 41:51.743
What's happening?
Who are these people?

41:54.245 --> 41:55.446
They're my village.

41:55.547 --> 41:57.616
-No, boo.
-You ruined it.

41:57.716 --> 41:59.718
Dad, you've got
to tighten up.

42:02.888 --> 42:04.956
**

42:05.056 --> 42:07.292
Mwah. Look at you
not asking for a scarf.

42:07.392 --> 42:08.293
Soph.

42:08.393 --> 42:11.597
-TOGETHER: No weakness!
-Yes. Ow.

42:11.697 --> 42:13.031
Rory.
-Douglas.

42:13.131 --> 42:15.967
BOTH: Rock, squat, pause.
Rock, squat, pause.

42:16.067 --> 42:18.036
-The -- The pause is a bounce.
-Oh, a bounce.

42:18.136 --> 42:21.139
(gasps) Guys. Zoe.
She's going for Graham.

42:21.239 --> 42:22.974
Don't let the bunny ears
fool you.

42:23.074 --> 42:25.777
She's a cold-blooded killer!
-Hey, hey, hey, hang on.

42:25.877 --> 42:27.412
He's got this.

42:27.512 --> 42:29.280
I got your e-mail.

42:30.481 --> 42:32.884
It shook me
to my core.

42:32.984 --> 42:36.888
**

42:36.988 --> 42:40.826
**

42:40.926 --> 42:42.327
She likes him.

42:42.427 --> 42:45.897
(gasps) That Easter freak
likes my kid!

42:45.997 --> 42:49.400
Aww, and they're sharing gum.
That's huge.

42:49.500 --> 42:50.602
It's gross.
-It is gross.

42:50.702 --> 42:51.837
But it's -- it's huge.

42:51.937 --> 42:54.773
I told you. Mush works.

42:54.873 --> 42:57.442
And from now on,
I will eat at restaurants

42:57.542 --> 42:59.077
that don't give out crayons.
-Whoo!

42:59.177 --> 43:00.178
-Yeah!
-I'm gonna maybe

43:00.278 --> 43:02.914
start drinking coffee
after 4:00 p.m.

43:03.014 --> 43:04.115
-Whoo!
-Sounds fine.

43:04.215 --> 43:06.317
I am out of the vortex!

43:06.417 --> 43:07.853
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

43:07.953 --> 43:09.154
Okay.

43:09.254 --> 43:10.756
Don't go up the slide.

43:10.856 --> 43:12.691
-* Oh, baby, please
-He's a long way from sex.

43:12.791 --> 43:14.626
I am out of the vortex!

43:14.726 --> 43:17.328
-* Give a little respect
-I watched a guy get crushed
by a forklift,

43:17.428 --> 43:18.864
but this is worse.
-Word.

43:18.964 --> 43:20.766
Third time's the charm.

43:20.866 --> 43:21.700
(grunts)

43:21.800 --> 43:24.703
* To me

43:26.137 --> 43:28.006
I'm out of the vortex!
